The paper discusses a protocol for secure multi-party computation (SMC) for preserving privacy during data mining. This falls under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). The paper also mentions the use of SMC for privacy-preserving database query, which falls under the category of databases (cs.DB). The paper also discusses the use of SMC for scientific computations, which falls under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the use of SMC between competitors, which falls under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC).
